/*
If an element extends beyond the allocated width, how do you truncate the sentence with an ellipsis (...) using CSS?
For example, "Hello! I am an element, and my width is larger than the container..
Pick ONE OR MORE options
*/

(wrong)----->{ white-space: pre-wrap; overflow: ellipsis; }

(wrong)----->{ text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: wrap; visibility: hidden; }

(correct)----->{ white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }

(wrong)----->None of the above
